'''自证其罪'''（self-incrimination）是指自己在遇到法律訴訟時承認自己有罪的行为<ref>{{Cite book|title=Black's Law Dictionary|page=690|edition=5th|date=1979}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://scholarlycommons.law.northwestern.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=7148&context=jclc|title=The Self-Incrimination Clause Explained and Its Future Predicted|publisher=Journal of Criminal Law and Criminology|date=2004|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180720194026/https://scholarlycommons.law.northwestern.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=7148&context=jclc|archive-date=2018|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://law.yale.edu/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/Faculty/Langbein_Privilege_Against_Self_Incrimination.pdf|title=The Historical Origins of the Privilege Against Self-incrimination at Common Law|author=John H. Langbein|publisher=Michigan Law Review|date=1994|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423031254/https://law.yale.edu/sites/default/files/documents/pdf/Faculty/Langbein_Privilege_Against_Self_Incrimination.pdf|archive-date=2021|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://digitalcommons.law.yale.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1957&context=fss_papers|title=Fifh Amendment First Principles: The Self-incrimination Clause|publisher=Michigan Law Review|date=1995|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423031712/https://digitalcommons.law.yale.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1957&context=fss_papers|archive-date=2021|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://scholarship.law.upenn.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=8073&context=penn_law_review|title=Self-incrimination|publisher=University of Pennsylvania Law Review|date=1925|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423032509/https://scholarship.law.upenn.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=8073&context=penn_law_review|archive-date=2021|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://chicagounbound.uchicago.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=2492&context=journal_articles|title=Origins of the Privilege against Self-Incrimination: The Role of the European Ius Commune|publisher=New York University Law Review|date=1990|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423035055/https://chicagounbound.uchicago.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=2492&context=journal_articles|archive-date=2021|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://scholarship.law.wm.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1175&context=facpubs|title=The Privilege's Last Stand: The Privilege Against Self-Incrimination and the Right to Rebel Against the State|publisher=Brooklyn Law Review|date=1999|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423035728/https://scholarship.law.wm.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1175&context=facpubs|archive-date=2021|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://heinonline.org/hol-cgi-bin/get_pdf.cgi?handle=hein.journals/uclalr33&section=37|title=Is There a Rationale for the Privilege Against Self-Incrimination?|publisher=UCLA Law Review|author=David Dolinko|date=1985|access-date=2022-03-03|archive-date=2021-04-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423041500/https://heinonline.org/hol-cgi-bin/get_pdf.cgi?handle=hein.journals%2Fuclalr33&section=37|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://digitalcommons.law.scu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1860&context=facpubs|title=Privilege Against Self-Incrimination|publisher=California Defender|date=1994|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423040403/https://digitalcommons.law.scu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1860&context=facpubs|archive-date=2021|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://open.mitchellhamline.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=2369&context=wmlr|title=The Privilege Against Compelled Self-incrimination|publisher=William Mitchell Law Review|date=1990|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423040626/https://open.mitchellhamline.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=2369&context=wmlr|archive-date=2021|dead-url=no}}</ref>。自证其罪可分為直接自证其罪或间接自证其罪，一個人如果是在审讯時承認自己有罪，則屬於直接自证其罪；而在没有他人压力的情况下自愿坦白自己犯罪行為的則屬於間接自证其罪<ref>{{Cite book|title=Essentials of criminal justice|last=1947-|first=Siegel, Larry J.|others=Worrall, John L.|isbn=978-1305633766|edition=Tenth|location=Australia|oclc=960166637|year=2017}}</ref>。

许多國家的法律規定，不能强迫被指控的嫌疑犯自证其罪，當然，也沒有自證無罪的義務，嫌疑犯可以选择在審訊時自願向警察坦白，但[[警察|警察]]不能因嫌犯拒绝坦白而惩罚嫌疑犯。嫌疑犯有[[緘默權|保持沉默的权利]]和获得辯護律師的权利<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Right to Remain Silent Around the World|url=https://fas.org/blogs/secrecy/2016/06/miranda/|author=Aftergood|first=Steven|work=Federation of American Scientists|access-date=2021-01-28|archive-date=2021-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210506213239/https://fas.org/blogs/secrecy/2016/06/miranda/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://digitalcommons.tourolaw.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1140&context=scholarlyworks|title=The Talmudic Rule Against Self-Incrimination and the American Exclusionary Rule: A Societal Prohibition Versus an Affirmative Individual Right|publisher=Touro Law Center|date=2001|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423041714/https://digitalcommons.tourolaw.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1140&context=scholarlyworks|archive-date=2021|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://digitalcommons.law.villanova.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1489&context=vlr|title=Witness Privilege against Self-Incrimination in the Civil Law|publisher=Villanova Law Review|date=1960|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423042357/https://digitalcommons.law.villanova.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1489&context=vlr|archive-date=2021|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://digitalcommons.nyls.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1357&context=journal_of_international_and_comparative_law|title=A Comparative Discussion of the Privilege Against Self-incrimination|publisher=NYLS Journal of International and Comparative Law|date=1993|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423042520/https://digitalcommons.nyls.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1357&context=journal_of_international_and_comparative_law|archive-date=2021|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

